      "content": "thanks. it's a good start but honestly the part about \"avoiding divisive rhetoric\" feels a bit out of place for a campaign rally. we aren't looking to be diplomatic, we're looking to win. can you make it even more aggressive? i want you to lean harder into the idea that these progressive policies aren't just \"change\" but are actually an existential threat to the American way of life. use more punchy, decisive language that paints the opposition as a direct danger to our homes and children.",
